CSS
----
selector {
		 [property:property value;]<--declaration
}

Selector: html element name rule is applied to
declaration: statement of a rule
property: variable like color

can list multiple selectors/element types to apply the same rules to, separated by commas

Selector types
-element (as above)
-id <p id='myid'> ; id can only identify one element
-class just like id but can label several tags
-by other attribute e.g. img[src] or a[url]
-conditional e.g. a:hover when you hover over a link